    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "UNITED\nAIR LINES\nThe\nMAIN LINE AIRWAY\nThe Year 'Round Route\nEFFECTIVE NOVEMBER 1. 1939",
      "VANCOUVEH\nCANADA\nTACOMA\nPORTLAN\nDude\nLates\nDENVER\nSAN\nZion\noulder Dam\nLOS ANGELE\nSAN DIEGO\n• To Mexico City\nUNITED\nAIR LINES\nYEAR 'ROUND\nTHE\nMAIN LINE AIRWAY\nTWENTY years ago the Federal Gov-\nernment decided to develop the\nfirst coast-to-coast airway. With the\nwhole country to choose from, the route\nthat is today United's famous Main Line\nAirway was the one selected\n.. the\ndirect, short mid-continent route linking\nNEW YORK\nUNITED AIR LINES\nConnecting Air Lines\n• Rail Lines •... Highways\nTo Cuba, Cel\nthe East, the Great Lakes region, and\nthe Mid-West with the entire Pacific\nCoast.\nOver this favored airway United has\nattained the unmatched record of\n140,000,000 miles of flying, including\n30,000 coast-to-coast flights and 55,000\nChicago-New York flights.\nAnd over this route United provides\nthe fastest, shortest service between the\nEast and\nmost Pacific coast cities, in-\ncluding its famous coast-to-coast Main-\nliner sleeper service."
    ],
